Diff_Mod.AI_Compensation:
{AI Compensation}
			
												To give the AI a better start each owned hero gets additional units at day one and additional units to recruit in towns. The amount of additional units depends on the option {Neutral Stack Size} and {Double Stack Size}.
												The hero only gets level 1-3 units and not if he already has above 100 units in one slot. This option helps to solve the problem that the computer was sometimes unable to defeat the big stacks that could be generated at map start. The amount of additional units is roughly the same as the Stack Size option adds units to neutral stacks.

Diff_Mod.Mixed_Neutrals_Text:
{Mixed Neutrals Options}
			
												Regular neutrals on the adventure map are transformed into mixed neutrals. You can customize various settings like the degree of mixing, the appearance on the adventure map, the number of neutrals and more. The stacksize of mixed neutrals is calculated based on the fighting value of the monsters.
												Default values are stored in the {mixed neutrals.json} in the mod folder and can be changed by the player.

Diff_Mod.Option_23_Info:
{Stack Size for Humans}			
						
												The human stack size modifier increases the number of monsters you have to fight but only for the human player and not for the computer player. A value of 150% means that at map start a stack of 100 neutral monsters is increased to 150 monsters. This value is multiplicative with the General Stack Size value, so if you set both values to 200% the human player will face an 400% increased stack.
												
												Note: When used together with the {View exact  quantity} option the hint text about the monster size does not take into account the increased stack size for humans. Make right-click for the correct information.

